{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the admitted record. The key facts are:\n\n1. **The market title**: \"What will Trump say during the FIFA World Cup Draw?\" (PX-1)\n2. **The governing terms**: NEWMENTION rules (PX-2) define the underlying as words used by the entity during the specified time period, and allow event-based time periods.\n3. **The Kalshi source rule**: Video of the FIFA World Cup Draw is primary; if video consensus cannot be reached, transcripts of the FIFA World Cup Draw will be used (PX-4/DX-S2).\n4. **The utterance**: Trump said \"Ronaldo\" multiple times in the GovInfo transcript (PX-3/DX-2/DX-S3), which is officially titled **\"Remarks in an Exchange With Reporters Prior to the 2026 FIFA World Cup Draw\"** at the Kennedy Center at 11:13 a.m.\n5. **The formal draw transcript**: No \"Ronaldo\" match found in the formal FIFA World Cup Drawing transcript (DX-1/PX-R1/DX-S1).\n\nThe decisive issue is timing. The GovInfo source explicitly states the remarks were \"Prior to\" the draw, and the transcript shows Trump and Infantino were \"a little late to get in there\" while \"They wait\"—confirming the exchange happened *before* entering the formal program.\n\nThe Kalshi rule specifies using video/transcripts **of the FIFA World Cup Draw**. The formal draw transcript (DX-1) contains no Ronaldo. The only admitted source with Ronaldo is the pre-draw reporter exchange.\n\nUnder a preponderance standard, the market's source rule and ordinary meaning of \"during\" favor the formal draw period, not pre-program remarks, even if they were at the same venue and event-related. Plaintiff has not shown the pre-program exchange qualifies as \"during\" or \"as part of\" the FIFA World Cup Draw for this market."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"HMYRmNXUw","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"not_demo